1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:03,340
Nesting conditions is a powerful technique in Python

2

00:00:03,340  -->  00:00:07,420
that allows us to add layers to our decision making process.

3

00:00:07,420  -->  00:00:10,400
By placing one if statement inside another,

4

00:00:10,400  -->  00:00:12,500
we create a hierarchy of checks,

5

00:00:12,500  -->  00:00:17,895
where each subsequent decision is made only if the previous condition is met.

6

00:00:17,895  -->  00:00:22,690
This approach is particularly useful when one condition is dependent on another.

7

00:00:22,690  -->  00:00:27,670
For example, you might check if a user is logged in before verifying their permissions.

8

00:00:27,670  -->  00:00:31,950
If they're not logged in, there's no need to proceed with the permission check.

9

00:00:31,950  -->  00:00:36,510
Nesting also helps break down complex logic into manageable parts,

10

00:00:36,510  -->  00:00:39,490
making it easier to handle intricate scenarios,

11

00:00:39,490  -->  00:00:43,390
such as validating multiple user inputs in a specific order,

12

00:00:43,390  -->  00:00:47,810
guiding users through multi set processes or navigating through decision trees.

13

00:00:47,810  -->  00:00:52,840
Let's look at an example of how nested conditional statements work in practice.

14

00:00:52,840  -->  00:00:56,040
To see how conditionals work with nesting,

15

00:00:56,040  -->  00:00:59,180
we're going to refactor our previous python code with

16

00:00:59,180  -->  00:01:03,180
the weather example that use conditional statements with logical operators

17

00:01:03,180  -->  00:01:06,720
into new python code that uses a nested structure

18

00:01:06,720  -->  00:01:10,980
with if else keywords to accomplish the same exact goal.

19

00:01:10,980  -->  00:01:17,040
We'll start by checking if the temperature is greater than 77 degrees Fahrenheit.

20

00:01:17,040  -->  00:01:20,300
If it is, we'll then evaluate whether it's sunny or not.

21

00:01:20,300  -->  00:01:21,900
If both conditions are met,

22

00:01:21,900  -->  00:01:23,440
we'll print, go to the beach.

23

00:01:23,440  -->  00:01:26,615
If it's not sunny, we'll print, stay inside.

24

00:01:26,615  -->  00:01:29,680
What we'll do is we'll remove

25

00:01:29,680  -->  00:01:34,920
that end component and we'll keep if temperature is greater than 77.

26

00:01:34,920  -->  00:01:38,980
We're then going to add if and else.

27

00:01:38,980  -->  00:01:42,095
If is going to be if sunny.

28

00:01:42,095  -->  00:01:46,515
We're going to take our print statement here and move that up here.

29

00:01:46,515  -->  00:01:49,140
If it's sunny, print, go to the beach.

30

00:01:49,140  -->  00:01:57,270
Else we'll print, stay inside.

31

00:01:57,270  -->  00:02:00,390
Now, we'll write elif,

32

00:02:00,390  -->  00:02:04,065
and we'll say if elif temperature is greater than 50,

33

00:02:04,065  -->  00:02:07,380
we'll remove this and not is sunny component,

34

00:02:07,380  -->  00:02:09,160
and we'll do the same exact thing.

35

00:02:09,160  -->  00:02:11,200
We'll copy this code here.

36

00:02:11,200  -->  00:02:13,460
We're going to remove this part.

37

00:02:13,460  -->  00:02:17,420
We'll paste that in there. Then we're going to say, if is sunny.

38

00:02:17,420  -->  00:02:19,760
So if it's greater than 50 and is sunny,

39

00:02:19,760  -->  00:02:23,330
we're going to say, go for a walk.

40

00:02:25,880  -->  00:02:29,790
Else we'll print, stay inside.

41

00:02:29,790  -->  00:02:34,690
Else we'll then print, stay inside.

42

00:02:35,830  -->  00:02:41,430
So if the temperature is not greater than 77 degrees,

43

00:02:41,430  -->  00:02:45,430
we're going to go down to the elif statement right here,

44

00:02:45,430  -->  00:02:51,330
and we move further down to the else block to check if it's greater than 50.

45

00:02:51,330  -->  00:02:52,750
If it's less than 50,

46

00:02:52,750  -->  00:02:56,270
that's where the else clause will be initiated.

47

00:02:56,270  -->  00:03:00,790
Within this block, we'll nest another statement to check if it's sunny,

48

00:03:00,790  -->  00:03:02,080
so that's why we're printing,

49

00:03:02,080  -->  00:03:04,410
go for a walk here in this nested structure.

50

00:03:04,410  -->  00:03:08,705
Otherwise, in the nested structure we'll print, stay inside.

51

00:03:08,705  -->  00:03:13,850
Finally, if the temperature is 50 degrees or below,

52

00:03:13,850  -->  00:03:15,890
that's this else clause here,

53

00:03:15,890  -->  00:03:17,910
the program advises us to stay inside

54

00:03:17,910  -->  00:03:21,350
directly as seen with this else statement at the end.

55

00:03:21,350  -->  00:03:24,920
Now, let's run some tests as we did before.

56

00:03:24,920  -->  00:03:28,710
When the temperature is 80 and it's sunny,

57

00:03:28,710  -->  00:03:30,890
so we'll change that to true.

58

00:03:31,050  -->  00:03:34,430
What do you think the output will be here?

59

00:03:34,430  -->  00:03:38,150
If we run this, we'll see, go to the beach.

60

00:03:38,150  -->  00:03:40,190
So if you said, go to the beach, you're right,

61

00:03:40,190  -->  00:03:42,770
and that's because the first statement is picking up on both of

62

00:03:42,770  -->  00:03:46,310
these conditions being true. Right there.

63

00:03:46,310  -->  00:03:50,810
If the temperature is greater than 77 and is sunny.

64

00:03:51,220  -->  00:03:54,460
Now, what if the temperature is 20?

65

00:03:54,660  -->  00:03:57,900
What do you think the output will be here?

66

00:03:57,900  -->  00:04:01,065
Let's run it and see and find out.

67

00:04:01,065  -->  00:04:03,685
This says stand side,

68

00:04:03,685  -->  00:04:08,060
and we see stand side because the else statement is covering everything

69

00:04:08,060  -->  00:04:14,260
below 50 degrees and including 50 degrees regardless of the sunny part.

70

00:04:14,340  -->  00:04:18,100
As soon as our temperature reaches 50,

71

00:04:18,100  -->  00:04:25,020
will this fire off one of these statements here? Let's find out.

72

00:04:29,030  -->  00:04:31,670
When it's 50 and is sunny,

73

00:04:31,670  -->  00:04:34,080
we see stay inside,

74

00:04:34,080  -->  00:04:39,175
and that's because it's not greater than 50. It's exactly 50.

75

00:04:39,175  -->  00:04:43,410
That's what gets picked up by this else clause here,

76

00:04:43,410  -->  00:04:45,465
and that's why we see this in the output.

77

00:04:45,465  -->  00:04:49,570
Ultimately, when the temperature is 51 degrees,

78

00:04:49,570  -->  00:04:55,270
what do you think will happen with the output now?

79

00:04:56,900  -->  00:05:00,670
We'll see go for a walk,

80

00:05:00,770  -->  00:05:06,020
and that's because the third conditional statement where the temperature is

81

00:05:06,020  -->  00:05:11,560
greater than 50 and is sunny is happening right there.

82

00:05:11,560  -->  00:05:14,820
By nesting these conditional statements,

83

00:05:14,820  -->  00:05:18,320
we've added more structure and clarity to our decision making process.

84

00:05:18,320  -->  00:05:21,320
Each layer of logic is clearly separated,

85

00:05:21,320  -->  00:05:25,400
making it easier to manage and adapt to changes.
